article.headline: W. Michigan 84, E. Michigan 80
article.story: KALAMAZOO, Mich. (AP) -- David Kool scored 12 of his career-high 26 points in the final 2:08, helping Western Michigan defeat Eastern Michigan 84-80 on Saturday afternoon. Kool, a freshman guard, hit two 3-pointers and six consecutive free throws in the game's final minutes as the Broncos (8-10, 3-2 Mid-American) won their seventh consecutive home game and defeated the Eagles for the eighth straight time. Kool hit 70 percent of his shots (7-of-10), including 4-of-5 from 3-point range, and did not commit a turnover in 30 minutes. Carlos Medlock scored 21 points for Eastern Michigan (7-11, 2-3) and Zane Gay came off the bench to score a career-high 16 points. Joe Reitz added 18 points and a team-high seven rebounds for Western Michigan. Michael Redell scored 16 and had a game-high eight assists. Freshman Justin Dobbins tied a career high with 12 points and had a game-high eight rebounds for the Eagles, who outrebounded the Broncos 35-27 -- the first time in the past 11 games Western was outrebounded. Neither team led by more than seven points, and the lead changed hands 18 times before Kool took charge down the stretch.
